    "discriminators": [
     "Destruction, not contact: a violent broadband crack followed by a splintering micro-transient tail. High spectral_flux and near-zero harmonicity distinguish it from WOODImpt, a clean single impulse that leaves the piece intact.",
     "Against WOODCrsh: a BREAK is the moment of fracture — one destructive event with a splinter tail. A CRASH is the aftermath — a longer, multi-event scene of pieces landing and settling. Duration and transient_count carry the split.",
     "A snapping dowel is short and sharp; a shattering plank is broader and noisier. Both stay under a couple of seconds."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "WOODCrsh",
