    "discriminators": [
     "The wood material reference. A singular hit: instant attack, front-loaded envelope, and a ring that COLLAPSES — decay_time_seconds_60db around 0.05-0.2 s. Say the boundary plainly: METAL-IMPACT rings roughly an order of magnitude longer (~0.5-2 s) with high inharmonicity and a dense partial_count. Ring time is the material-impedance axis and the single most diagnostic feature in this file.",
     "Against WOODBrk: an impact leaves the board intact — one clean impulse, low spectral_flux, no splinter tail. A break is broadband, noisy and destructive.",
     "Against WOODCrsh: singular versus group. The explanation says group wood destruction goes to CRASH.",
     "Against WOODHndl: same event class, far higher level and crest factor. A bonk is not a set-down."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "WOODBrk",
     "WOODCrsh",
     "WOODHndl",
     "DOORKnck"
    ]
